summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Tenth Avenue Northeast, in the City of Seattle, from East Sixty-fifth Street to Sylvester Place, by grading and curbing the same, together with the necessary drainage, in accordance with Majority Petition, being File No. 34083; and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
